history.content: Yes the schedule sounds reasonable and you should probably phase 1 161 and 168.

children.subject:
I took the exact same 3 classes last semester! It is going to be pretty tough as those 3 classes have considerably more projects than 170,188 and 186 which have fewer and shorter projects. There was also a lot of overlap among the projects in the 3 classes which made it pretty stressful at times. 

I would phase 1 168 for sure and then maybe 161. 168 is only offered in the Fall I think. And normally 162 doesn't get filled up too quickly as it is a considerably tougher class.

161 was the easiest and least time consuming out of the 3. It is going to probably be different among professors, but I would consider it more like 186 this semester (except 161 has homeworks AND projects). You have midterms, a couple of projects and then for my semester, 161 had homework every week. The lecture and project material was very interesting though!

168 was probably the next easiest. You had 4 homeworks and 4 projects. The homeworks were not bad, the projects were alright, but had a lot of edge cases you had to pass. This was my most favorite class as the professor and material was fun! 

162 was the hardest. You are in a group of 4 people and do 3 group projects with the entire semester. These projects are nothing to joke about, they are ridiculously time consuming and tough. Probably nothing like any other class project before, and it's also in C, which makes it twice as fun. You had around 5 homeworks which were like the 186/161 projects. But this is a good class and you do learn how to work in a group and you learn alot of material.

So it might be a tough semester especially if the projects/midterms within the classes overlap, so use your time well! Good luck! =D
